 Maybe it is even unrealistic or unphysical.
 Indeed value of ds<0 would require the adhesive pad (or its backing layer)
 to pass through the adhering underlying surface.
 I believe this cannot occur in reality and must be excluded from the analysis.
 One, then, concludes that the reduction factor for the "flex" is very close
